All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ant
    Class Ant that identifies an ant, its path and the weight of its path
    Colony
    Class which defines the colony.
    Evaporation
    Abstract class that extends an event for a specific type Evaporation
    EvaporationEdge
    Class which defines an evaporation event for this specific population simulation and triggers it
    Events
    Abstract Class where an event of the simulation is defined (to be added in the PEC) All the events have the event time attribute in common, and so when the object of this class is created, the event time is schedule (for the given time).
    Graph
    Class that saves all the information about the graph, including the number of node, the nest and implements the adjacency list and the respective methods.
    GraphInterface
    Interface for the graph, where are define the methods implemented in the Graph Package.
    Input
    Parser function
    Main
    Project of Object Oriented Programming:
    Move
    Abstract class that extends an event for a specific type Move and moves one individual of a population
    MoveAnt
    Class which defines a move event for this specific population simulation and triggers it
    Node
    Class that implements the adjacency list
    Observation
    Abstract class that extends an event Observation
    ObservationState
    Class which defines an observation event and triggers it
    PEC
    Class that implements a Pending Event Container (PEC), where the Events are added and saved, in the correct order in a Priority Queue, and triggered.
    Simulation
    Abstract class where is define a Stochastic Simulation based on the event occurence.
    SimulationColony
    Class which manages the colony simulation.
    UpdateEvaporation
    Class that will handle the evaporation updates on a specific edge.
    UpdateMoveAnt
    Class which handle the movement of the ants in the colony
    Weight
    Class that stores the information about an edge and the correspondent weight and pheromone level
